  "texts": [
    "disc-like, bi-conic, bowl-like) and kinematics (Keplerian rotation, inflow, outflow) of BLR gas is yet limited despite of more than fifty years of investigation.",
    "The physical conditions in the BLR are explored through advanced photoionization codes, such as the state-of-the-art code CLOUDY (Ferland et al. 2013).",
    "This code enables one to reproduce most of the line ratios observed in AGN and has improved our understanding of the chemical evolution of AGN host galaxies (Nagao et al. 2006).",
    "Some challenges remain, however, such as reproducing the iron multiplet or the ratio between optical and UV Fe II emission, which shows a large scatter at the population level (Ferland et al. 2009; Sarkar et al. 2021).",
    "Our inability to accurately reproduce this major component of AGN spectra is likely linked to uncertainties on the distribution and kinematics of the iron emission in the BLR (Ferland et al. 2009)."
  ]
}